            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It’s also a pain to sell a motorcycle by listing on a site like Craigslist. After all, you can get a bunch of lookie-loos who aren’t the least bit serious about buying the bike. Then there are the low-ballers who seem to think the whole point is to try talking you way down before even seeing the thing. Joyriders who just want to feel what it’s like to ride your motorcycle without buying it, and worse aren’t very good at riding, are another negative. And there are others who make an appointment only to never show up.",
